All Implemented Interfaces:
ArrayObject<T>, ObjectLike
public class JsHTMLCollection<T extends JsHTMLElement>
extends DOM2HTML.HTMLCollection.Prototype<T>
implements ArrayObject<T>

An opaque class representing JavaScript client-side objects of the global JsClient.HTMLCollection class.

An object of this class is a collection of HTML elements with methods that allow you to retrieve an element by its position in the collection or by its JsHTMLElement.id or name attribute. In JavaScript, a JsHTMLCollection object behaves like a read-only array, and you can use JavaScript square-bracket notation to index the array by number or by name instead of calling the item(Number) and namedItem(String) methods.

A number of the properties of the JsHTMLDocument object are JsHTMLCollection objects and provide convenient access to document elements such as forms, images, and links. The JsHTMLFormElement.elements and JsHTMLSelectElement.options are also objects of this class. This class provides a convenient way to traverse the rows of a JsHTMLTableElement and the cells of a JsHTMLTableRowElement.

Objects of this class are read-only. You cannot assign new elements to them, even when using JavaScript array notation. They are live, meaning that if the underlying document changes, those changes are immediately visible through all JsHTMLCollection objects.

This class is similar to JsNodeList but its objects may be indexed by name as well as by number.

Author:
J.J.Liu (Jianjun Liu) at http://www.jscripter.org
See Also:
